HEADWORD: Nucleoplasmic
<hw>Nu`cle*o*plas"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to nucleoplasm; -- esp. applied
to a body formed in the developing ovum from the plasma of the nucleus
of the germinal vesicle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nucleoside</ent>⟦br⟧
